---
title: "Sequence Diagram: Authentication Service"
---
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant FE  as Frontend<br/>(React/Ionic)
    participant AS  as AuthService<br/>(port 8000)
    participant DB  as PostgreSQL

    Note over User,DB: ── STEP 1: Submit Credentials ──────────────────────────

    User ->> FE  : Enter email & password
    activate FE
    FE   ->> AS  : POST /api/v1/auth/login {email, password}
    activate AS
    AS   ->> DB  : SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = ?
    activate DB
    DB  -->> AS  : User record | None
    deactivate DB

    AS   ->> AS  : PasswordHasher.verify(raw, hash)<br/>User.is_locked() → check lockout_until

    alt User not found OR not verified
        AS  -->> FE  : 401 { detail: "Invalid credentials" }
        FE  -->> User : Show error message
    else Account locked (failed_login_attempts ≥ 3)
        AS  -->> FE  : 423 { detail: "Account locked for 1 hour" }
        FE  -->> User : Show lockout timer
    else Wrong password (attempts < 3)
        AS   ->> DB  : UPDATE users SET failed_login_attempts = N
        activate DB
        DB  -->> AS  : OK
        deactivate DB
        AS  -->> FE  : 401 { detail: "Invalid credentials. Attempt N/3" }
        FE  -->> User : "Wrong password (N/3 attempts)"
    else Correct password
        AS   ->> DB  : UPDATE users SET failed_login_attempts = 0
        activate DB
        DB  -->> AS  : OK
        deactivate DB
        AS   ->> DB  : INSERT INTO otps<br/>(purpose=LOGIN_2FA, expires=NOW()+10min)
        activate DB
        DB  -->> AS  : OTP record
        deactivate DB
        AS   ->> AS  : EmailSender.send_2fa_email(email, otp_code)
        AS  -->> FE  : 200 { message: "OTP sent", pending_2fa: true }
        deactivate AS
        FE  -->> User : "Enter the OTP sent to your email"
    end

    Note over User,DB: ── STEP 2: Confirm 2FA OTP ─────────────────────────────

    User ->> FE  : Enter 6-digit OTP
    FE   ->> AS  : POST /api/v1/auth/login/confirm {email, otp_code}
    activate AS
    AS   ->> DB  : SELECT * FROM otps<br/>WHERE code=? AND purpose=LOGIN_2FA<br/>AND expires_at > NOW() AND is_used=False
    activate DB
    DB  -->> AS  : OTP | None
    deactivate DB

    alt OTP invalid or expired
        AS  -->> FE  : 401 { detail: "Invalid or expired OTP" }
        FE  -->> User : Show error
    else OTP valid
        AS   ->> DB  : UPDATE otps SET is_used = TRUE<br/>UPDATE users SET last_login = NOW()
        activate DB
        DB  -->> AS  : OK
        deactivate DB
        AS   ->> AS  : JWTHandler.create_token_pair(user_id, email)<br/>→ access_token (15 min) + refresh_token (7 days)
        AS  -->> FE  : 200 { access_token, refresh_token }
        deactivate AS
        FE  -->> User : Store tokens → Redirect to Dashboard
    end

    deactivate FE
